  <div class="container">
    <div class="text-center fade-in">
      <h2 class="section-title">The Benchmark</h2>
      <p class="section-subtitle">
        A multi-axis framework for fair and meaningful evaluation of bimanual manipulation systems.
      </p>
    </div>

    <p class="benchmark-intro text-center fade-in">
      Current bimanual manipulation benchmarks are fragmented across hardware platforms, task definitions,
      and evaluation criteria. Our workshop targets the design of a community-wide standard covering
      task diversity, generalization, robustness, and deployment readiness — evaluated on real robots
      under standardized conditions.
    </p>

    <div class="benchmark-pillars fade-in">
      <div class="pillar">
        <div class="pillar-number">01</div>
        <h3>Task Suite</h3>
        <p>Three core tasks: cable routing, deformable material handling (thermal pad placement), and assisted living &amp; feeding.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="pillar">
        <div class="pillar-number">02</div>
        <h3>Metrics</h3>
        <p>Success rate, precision, cycle time, generalization score, and human-comparative performance.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="pillar">
        <div class="pillar-number">03</div>
        <h3>Data Protocol</h3>
        <p>Shared teleoperation, annotation schema, and hardware calibration guidelines for cross-site compatibility.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="pillar">
        <div class="pillar-number">04</div>
        <h3>Hardware Agnosticism</h3>
        <p>Platform-neutral APIs and sim-to-real transfer tracks to include diverse robot embodiments.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="pillar">
        <div class="pillar-number">05</div>
        <h3>Leaderboard</h3>
        <p>An open, continuously updated leaderboard with verified real-robot submissions.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="pillar">
        <div class="pillar-number">06</div>
        <h3>Open Dataset</h3>
        <p>Curated multi-site demonstration dataset with diverse operators, environments, and objects.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>


<!-- ============================================================
     BENCHMARK TASKS
     ============================================================ -->
<section id="tasks">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="text-center fade-in">
      <h2 class="section-title">Benchmark Tasks</h2>
      <p class="section-subtitle">
        Three core bimanual manipulation tasks — contact-rich assembly, deformable material handling, and assisted living. Tasks run in Isaac Sim, MuJoCo, and Genesis.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="tasks-grid fade-in">

      <!-- Task 1 -->
      <div class="task-card">
        <div class="task-img" style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, #0a2a4a 0%, #00b4d8 100%);">
          <div class="task-img-label">
            <span>Task</span>
            <strong>01</strong>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="task-body">
          <h3 class="task-title">Cable Routing &amp; Plugging</h3>
          <p class="task-scenario">Industrial path recognition, cable grasping, routing, and fixation.</p>

          <div class="task-block">
            <span class="task-label">Objectives</span>
            <ul class="task-list">
              <li>Route the cable around O-props and through C-props sequentially</li>
              <li>Reach Y-checkpoints to validate preceding scores</li>
              <li>Maintain tension and bimanual coordination for Y-props</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="task-block">
            <span class="task-label">Technical challenges</span>
            <p class="task-text">Deformable-object manipulation (flexible cable), contact-rich interaction &amp; path recognition, and bimanual re-grasping with dual-arm coordination.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="task-block">
            <span class="task-label">Evaluation</span>
            <p class="task-text"><strong>Primary:</strong> validated scoring points (total, within 20 min). <strong>Secondary:</strong> completion time, re-grasps, handovers. <strong>Process:</strong> SPARC smoothness, joint torque, bimanual metrics.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="task-sims">
            <span class="task-label">Simulators</span>
            <span class="sim-chip">Isaac Sim</span>
            <span class="sim-chip">MuJoCo</span>
          </div>

          <div class="task-tags">
            <span class="task-tag tag-cyan">Contact-Rich</span>
            <span class="task-tag tag-cyan">Deformable</span>
            <span class="task-tag tag-cyan">Bimanual</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Task 2 -->
      <div class="task-card">
        <div class="task-img" style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, #2d1b69 0%, #c026d3 100%);">
          <div class="task-img-label">
            <span>Task</span>
            <strong>02</strong>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="task-body">
          <h3 class="task-title">Deformable Material Handling (Thermal Pad Placement)</h3>
          <p class="task-scenario">Industrial electronics manufacturing — a Thermal Interface Material (TIM) assembly benchmark.</p>

          <div class="task-block">
            <span class="task-label">Objectives</span>
            <ul class="task-list">
              <li>Peel the thermal-pad liner from its substrate</li>
              <li>Transport the highly deformable pad without damage</li>
              <li>Align and attach it onto the designated PCB chip area</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="task-block">
            <span class="task-label">Technical challenges</span>
            <p class="task-text">Deformable-material modeling (soft-body physics), non-linear adhesion and surface friction, high-precision placement of compliant objects, and contact-rich force control with tactile sensing.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="task-block">
            <span class="task-label">Evaluation</span>
            <p class="task-text">Placement accuracy (center &amp; orientation), deformation quality &amp; wrinkle/folding ratio, process safety (force-threshold violations), and total completion time.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="task-sims">
            <span class="task-label">Simulators</span>
            <span class="sim-chip">Isaac Sim</span>
            <span class="sim-chip">MuJoCo</span>
            <span class="sim-chip">Genesis</span>
          </div>

          <div class="task-tags">
            <span class="task-tag tag-purple">Deformable</span>
            <span class="task-tag tag-purple">Precision</span>
            <span class="task-tag tag-purple">Tactile</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Task 3 -->
      <div class="task-card">
        <div class="task-img" style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, #7c2d12 0%, #f97316 100%);">
          <div class="task-img-label">
            <span>Task</span>
            <strong>03</strong>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="task-body">
          <h3 class="task-title">Assisted Living &amp; Feeding</h3>
          <p class="task-scenario">Assisted-living dining: Pick &rarr; Deliver &rarr; Feed &rarr; Collect.</p>

          <div class="task-block">
            <span class="task-label">Objectives</span>
            <ul class="task-list">
              <li>Pick, deliver in sequence (Stations A&ndash;H), and feed at Station I</li>
              <li>Bimanual feeding — one arm holds the spoon, one holds the container</li>
              <li>Return all objects to the Collection Area (yellow zone)</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="task-block">
            <span class="task-label">Environment</span>
            <p class="task-text">Start Zone, Pickup (gray), Delivery (A&ndash;H), and Feeding (I); objects are IKEA KALAS containers &amp; spoons. Simulation and real-world setups are identical.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="task-block">
            <span class="task-label">Evaluation</span>
            <p class="task-text"><strong>Primary:</strong> success points — Delivery / Feed / Collect (+10 each). <strong>Secondary:</strong> completion time, remaining food items. <strong>Safety:</strong> peak head force &amp; watchdog interventions.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="task-sims">
            <span class="task-label">Simulators</span>
            <span class="sim-chip">Isaac Sim</span>
            <span class="sim-chip">MuJoCo</span>
          </div>

          <div class="task-tags">
            <span class="task-tag tag-amber">Human-Centered</span>
            <span class="task-tag tag-amber">Safety-Critical</span>
            <span class="task-tag tag-amber">Bimanual</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>


    </div><!-- /.tasks-grid -->

    <p class="tasks-note fade-in">
      Reference simulation environments and full scoring scripts will be released as part of the benchmark framework.
    </p>

  </div>
</section>


